[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Why Consistify ‚ùì[m
[32m+[m[32mMany people need simple, personalized planning that balances workouts, nutrition and sleep while respecting budgets and exercise preferences. Consistify is designed to be a clear, extensible front-end prototype that demonstrates how to combine calorie math, budget-aware meal suggestions and workouts into a friendly UI ‚Äî with clear hooks to integrate robust nutrition and exercise APIs.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Features ‚ú®[m
[32m+[m[32m- Calorie calculator (Mifflin‚ÄìSt Jeor) + activity multipliers[m
[32m+[m[32m- Macro suggestions (protein, fat, carbs)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Filterable workout plans (home / gym / cardio / yoga)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Budget-aware diet plan suggestions with calorie match tolerance[m
[32m+[m[32m- Sleep & recovery tips that adapt to age and activity[m
[32m+[m[32m- Accessible UI built with Bootstrap[m
[32m+[m[32m- Image-rich, responsive layouts (Unsplash placeholder images)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Clear extension points for nutrition/exercise API integration[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Demo / Screenshots üñºÔ∏è[m
[32m+[m[32m(Screenshots are placeholders ‚Äî replace with your own when available)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Hero with background + CTA[m
[32m+[m[32m- Workout & diet cards with images[m
[32m+[m[32m- Calorie & macro calculator panel[m
[32m+[m[32m- Plan summary card with selected options[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Tech stack üß∞[m
[32m+[m[32m- Frontend: HTML, CSS (Bootstrap + custom), vanilla JavaScript[m
[32m+[m[32m- Prototype images: Unsplash (ensure compliance with Unsplash license for production)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Recommended backend (for production & API keys): Node.js + Express (or serverless on Vercel / AWS Lambda)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Optional DB: PostgreSQL / MongoDB for user accounts and saved plans[m
[32m+[m[32m- Mobile: React Native or Flutter (recommended) for Android & iOS[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Local setup ‚Äî Getting started üöÄ[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPrerequisites:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Node.js >= 14 (only required for local web servers or backend)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Optional: yarn / npm[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mQuick static preview:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Open `src/client/index.html` in a browser for a static preview.[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Or run a static server (recommended):[m
[32m+[m[32m   - npm i -g serve[m
[32m+[m[32m   - cd src/client && serve .[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFor development with a backend:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Add a small Express server in `src/server/` to proxy nutrition or exercise API requests (keeps API keys secret).[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Start the frontend static server and the backend concurrently during development.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## How it works ‚Äî high level üß≠[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. User enters weight, height, age, gender, activity level, preferences and budget.[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Client computes BMR (Mifflin‚ÄìSt Jeor) and maintenance calories:[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Male: BMR = 10*kg + 6.25*cm ‚àí 5*age + 5[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Female: BMR = 10*kg + 6.25*cm ‚àí 5*age ‚àí 161[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Other: a safe averaged fallback[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Maintenance calories = BMR √ó activityFactor (sedentary ‚Üí very active)[m
[32m+[m[32m4. App suggests macros:[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Protein ~ 1.2‚Äì2.2 g/kg (configurable)[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Fat ~ 25% of calories (example)[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Carbs fill remaining calories[m
[32m+[m[32m5. The front-end filters sample workout/diet cards using preferences & budget. For production, the backend will generate meal combinations that meet calorie/macros & budget using nutrition API nutrient data.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## API integration & data flow üîó[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRecommended APIs:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Edamam Nutrition API (detailed nutrients)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Nutritionix (food + exercise)[m
[32m+[m[32m- USDA FoodData Central (open nutrient database)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Spoonacular (recipes & cost estimates)[m
[32m+[m[32m- ExerciseDB (exercise metadata & video links)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIntegration pattern:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Frontend collects user inputs.[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Frontend calls your backend:[m
[32m+[m[32m   - POST /api/meal-plan { calories, macros, budget, dietaryPrefs }[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Backend:[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Queries nutrition API(s) for candidate foods/recipes[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Solves for meal combos that balance calories/macros within budget (server-side algorithm)[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Returns structured plan: meals, nutrient totals, cost estimate[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Frontend displays meals, shopping list and allows selection[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mSecurity note:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Never embed API keys in client-side JS. Keep all keys in server-side environment variables or use a secrets store.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mExample server endpoint (pseudo):[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mPOST /api/meal-plan[m
[32m+[m[32mBody:[m
[32m+[m[32m{[m
[32m+[m[32m  "calories": 2000,[m
[32m+[m[32m  "protein": 120,[m
[32m+[m[32m  "budget": 6.5,[m
[32m+[m[32m  "preferences": { "vegan": false, "noNuts": true }[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mResponse:[m
[32m+[m[32m{[m
[32m+[m[32m  "meals": [ { "name": "Oat + banana", "calories": 450, "protein": 15, "cost": 1.2, "ingredients": [...] }, ... ],[m
[32m+[m[32m  "totals": { "calories": 2005, "protein": 123, "cost": 5.8}[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Algorithms & approach üß©[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mMeal planning with budget and nutrient constraints is a constrained optimization problem:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Consider knapsack / integer linear programming approaches for small-medium scale.[m
[32m+[m[32m- For speed, heuristics and greedy algorithms work well in a prototype:[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Pre-filter candidate foods in desired price ranges.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Greedy pack meals to meet calorie target, then adjust to fix macro deficits.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Use simple swaps (local search) to improve cost or nutrient fit.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mExercise energy estimation:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Use MET values or reliable API-provided calories burned per minute values.[m
[32m+[m[32m- For simple prototypes use estimates: calories/min = estCaloriesPerMin (per workout card).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Data model suggestions üóÇÔ∏è[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mUsers:[m
[32m+[m[32m- id, email (hashed), profile (weight, height, age, gender), preferences[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPlans:[m
[32m+[m[32m- userId, createdAt, goals {calories, protein}, selectedWorkouts[], selectedMeals[], summary[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFoods / Meals:[m
[32m+[m[32m- externalId, name, nutrients {calories, protein, carbs, fat, fiber, micros}, estimatedCost[m
[32m+[m
